==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cutpurse
<hw>Cut"purse`</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧t"p⟦ucir⟧rs`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>One who cuts purses for the sake of stealing them or their contents
(an act common when men wore purses fastened by a string to their
girdles); one who steals from the person; a pickpocket</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To have an open ear, a quick eye, and a nimble hand, is necessary
for a <qex>cutpurse</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cut-rate</ent>⟦br⟧
